Metadata: Solenolides, new antiinflammator​y and antiviral diterpenoids from a marine octocoral of the genus "Solenopodium"

Six new diterpenoid lactones, solenolides A-F, have been isolated from a new species of Indopacific gorgonian of the genus "Solenopodium". The solenolides are modifications of the well-known briarein class of marine metabolites, and several possess potent antiinflammator​y and antiviral properties.
